      "2d6d4370-2b46-474f-9cd5-15ebae28d481"],
     "\[LineSeparator]classically simulates the quantum information \
scrambling in ",
     ButtonBox["random Clifford circuits",
      BaseStyle->"Link",
      ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/RandomCliffordCircuit"],
     " on ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "e1684068-e9be-4ecb-bac5-3f34e09a74fb"],
     " qubits in terms of the out-of-time-order correlator ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      FormBox[
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"C", "(", "t", ")"}], ":=", 
        RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           SuperscriptBox["a", "\[Dagger]"], "(", "t", ")"}], 
          SuperscriptBox["b", "\[Dagger]"], 
          RowBox[{"a", "(", "t", ")"}], "b"}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]}], 
       TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
      "a0ab00c0-4ed6-4600-838f-2b950c1356d6"],
     ", where ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      FormBox["a", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
      "a2673942-4b6b-497d-870d-eb4cbdc9ecaf"],
     " and ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      FormBox["b", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
      "870ba9c8-7762-442a-982a-15af014f0d2e"],
     " are local Clifford unitary operators. For the remaining arguments ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["spec", "TI"], ",", 
       StyleBox["\[Ellipsis]", "TR"]}]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "7e1c953e-7d74-4c2d-ab28-591e47fc668f"],
     ", see ",
