    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "CliffordScramblingSimulate[{a, b}, spec, ...] classically simulates the \
quantum information scrambling in random Clifford circuits on n qubits in \
terms of the out-of-time-order correlator C(t) := \
\\[LeftAngleBracket]a^\\[Dagger] (t) b^\\[Dagger] a( t) \
b\\[RightAngleBracket], where a and b are local Clifford unitary operators. \
For the remaining arguments spec, ..., see RandomCliffordCircuit. \
CliffordScramblingSimulate[a, spec, ...] is equivalent to \
CliffordScramblingSimulate[{a, 1}, spec, ...].", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "CliffordScramblingSimulate", 
